The paper deals with the representation of graphs using axis-aligned strings in 3D space, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of graphs and their properties to study the complexity of string contact representations suggests that the paper may also belong to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses lower bounds on the complexity of string contact representations, which is a topic in computational complexity and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of Hamiltonian and bipartite graphs suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of structural informatics (cs.SI), which deals with the study of structural properties of complex systems.
